<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[178,1085,1304,1537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">
C o m m e n t s: The original description is based on a single female from &quot;Wadi Marba, Khamis Bushayt&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="COIFFAIT H" box="[449,605,1334,1356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" pagination="162 - 180" refId="ref5741" refString="COIFFAIT H. (1979): Insects of Saudi Arabia. Coleoptera: Fam. Staphylinidae, Subfam. Xantholinae [sic], Staphylininae, Paederinae, Oxytelinae, Aleocharinae. - Fauna of Saudi Arabia 1: 162 - 180." type="journal article" year="1979">COIFFAIT 1979</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[669,758,1334,1356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">holotype</typeStatus>
is undoubtedly congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1859" box="[178,256,1365,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[178,256,1365,1387]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1901" box="[309,407,1365,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punica">
<emphasis box="[309,407,1365,1387]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. punica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. If, indeed, it is even conspecific with the latter is a question that can only by answered when males become available from 
<collectingCountry box="[774,911,1395,1417]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[967,1056,1395,1417]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Coiffait" authorityYear="1978" box="[178,273,1425,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassa">
<emphasis box="[178,273,1425,1447]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. crassa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is highly similar to the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1901" box="[624,722,1425,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punica">
<emphasis box="[624,722,1425,1447]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. punica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seen from 
<collectingCountry box="[836,893,1425,1447]" name="Chad" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Chad</collectingCountry>
; it is distinguished only by the somewhat darker coloration and by the slightly smaller pronotum. For illustrations of the habitus and the forebody see 
<figureCitation box="[636,750,1485,1507]" captionStart="Figs 14-21" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1393,1413]" captionTargetBox="[183,1085,218,1368]" captionTargetId="figure-0@8.[178,1085,215,1385]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 14-21: Acanthoglossa punica FAUVEL from Chad (14-15), A. crassa COIFFAIT, holotype (16- 17), and Hypomedon niloticus (KOCH) (18-21): (14, 16, 18) habitus; (15, 17, 19) forebody; (20) male sternite VIII; (21) aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 14, 16, 18: 1.0 mm; 15, 17, 19: 0.5 mm; 20-21: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276557/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Figs 16-17</figureCitation>
. The species is currently known only from the type locality (Map 2).
</paragraph>
